---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms and Conditions | SESEC"
  description="Terms and conditions for SESEC cybersecurity consulting services. Legal terms governing the use of our services."
  lang="en"
>
  <Section title="Terms and Conditions" padding="xl">
    <div class="legal-content">
      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>1. Purpose</h3>
        <p>These terms and conditions govern the contractual relationship between SESEC and its clients for cybersecurity consulting services.</p>
        
        <p>By engaging our services, you agree to be bound by these terms and conditions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>2. Services</h3>
        
        <h4>2.1 Cybersecurity Consulting</h4>
        <p>SESEC provides professional cybersecurity consulting services including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Security assessments and audits</li>
          <li>Vulnerability testing and penetration testing</li>
          <li>Security architecture design</li>
          <li>Compliance consulting (ISO 27001, GDPR, etc.)</li>
          <li>Incident response and forensics</li>
          <li>Security training and awareness</li>
          <li>Risk management consulting</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>2.2 Service Delivery</h4>
        <p>Services are delivered according to agreed specifications, timelines, and methodologies outlined in individual service agreements.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>3. Contracting Process</h3>
        
        <h4>3.1 Service Agreement</h4>
        <p>Each engagement requires a written service agreement specifying:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Scope of work and deliverables</li>
          <li>Timeline and milestones</li>
          <li>Fees and payment terms</li>
          <li>Confidentiality requirements</li>
          <li>Liability limitations</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>3.2 Acceptance</h4>
        <p>Services commence upon signed agreement and receipt of any required advance payment.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>4. Client Obligations</h3>
        
        <h4>4.1 Cooperation</h4>
        <p>The client agrees to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide necessary access to systems and information</li>
          <li>Designate qualified personnel for coordination</li>
          <li>Respond promptly to requests for information</li>
          <li>Implement recommended security measures</li>
          <li>Maintain confidentiality of methodologies</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>4.2 System Access</h4>
        <p>Client is responsible for providing secure, authorized access to systems under assessment and ensuring all necessary permissions are obtained.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>5. Confidentiality</h3>
        
        <h4>5.1 Mutual Confidentiality</h4>
        <p>Both parties agree to maintain strict confidentiality regarding:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Proprietary information and trade secrets</li>
          <li>Security vulnerabilities and findings</li>
          <li>Business operations and strategies</li>
          <li>Technical methodologies and tools</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>5.2 Data Protection</h4>
        <p>SESEC implements appropriate safeguards to protect client data and complies with applicable data protection regulations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>6. Fees and Payment</h3>
        
        <h4>6.1 Fee Structure</h4>
        <p>Fees are determined based on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Scope and complexity of services</li>
          <li>Time and resources required</li>
          <li>Specialized expertise needed</li>
          <li>Urgency of delivery</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>6.2 Payment Terms</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Invoices are payable within 30 days of receipt</li>
          <li>Late payments may incur interest charges</li>
          <li>Advance payments may be required for certain services</li>
          <li>All fees are exclusive of applicable taxes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>7. Liability and Warranties</h3>
        
        <h4>7.1 Service Warranties</h4>
        <p>SESEC warrants that services will be performed:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>With professional skill and care</li>
          <li>In accordance with industry standards</li>
          <li>By qualified cybersecurity professionals</li>
          <li>Within agreed timelines</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>7.2 Limitation of Liability</h4>
        <p>SESEC's liability is limited to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Direct damages only (no consequential damages)</li>
          <li>Maximum amount equal to fees paid for the specific service</li>
          <li>Claims must be made within 12 months of service completion</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>7.3 Disclaimer</h4>
        <p>SESEC does not guarantee that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>All security vulnerabilities will be identified</li>
          <li>Systems will be immune from future attacks</li>
          <li>Compliance will be maintained indefinitely</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>8. Intellectual Property</h3>
        
        <h4>8.1 Deliverables</h4>
        <p>Client owns rights to specific deliverables created for their engagement, subject to SESEC's retained rights in methodologies and tools.</p>
        
        <h4>8.2 SESEC Property</h4>
        <p>SESEC retains ownership of:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Proprietary methodologies and frameworks</li>
          <li>Software tools and technologies</li>
          <li>General knowledge and experience</li>
          <li>Benchmark data and industry insights</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>9. Termination</h3>
        
        <h4>9.1 Termination Rights</h4>
        <p>Either party may terminate services:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>For material breach with 30 days written notice</li>
          <li>For convenience with 60 days written notice</li>
          <li>Immediately for insolvency or legal violations</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4>9.2 Effect of Termination</h4>
        <p>Upon termination:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Client pays for services performed to date</li>
          <li>Confidentiality obligations continue</li>
          <li>Work product is delivered in current state</li>
          <li>Each party returns confidential materials</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>10. Dispute Resolution</h3>
        
        <h4>10.1 Negotiation</h4>
        <p>Parties agree to first attempt resolution through good faith negotiation.</p>
        
        <h4>10.2 Mediation and Arbitration</h4>
        <p>Unresolved disputes will be subject to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Mediation before a qualified mediator</li>
          <li>Binding arbitration if mediation fails</li>
          <li>Proceedings conducted in Spain</li>
          <li>Spanish law governs interpretation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>11. Force Majeure</h3>
        <p>Neither party is liable for delays or failures due to circumstances beyond reasonable control, including natural disasters, government actions, or cyber attacks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>12. Modifications</h3>
        <p>These terms may be modified only by written agreement signed by both parties. Updates will be posted on our website with effective dates.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>13. Governing Law</h3>
        <p>These terms are governed by Spanish law. Spanish courts have exclusive jurisdiction over any disputes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h3>14. Contact Information</h3>
        <p>For questions about these terms:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:legal@sesecpro.com">legal@sesecpro.com</a></li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> +34 XXX XXX XXX</li>
          <li><strong>Address:</strong> Spain</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> January 2025</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  
  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }
  
  .legal-section h3 {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-size: var(--fs-h3);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  
  .legal-section h4 {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-size: var(--fs-lg);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-2) 0;
  }
  
  .legal-section p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  
  .legal-section ul {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }
  
  .legal-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  
  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--dur) var(--ease);
  }
  
  .legal-section a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-2);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-content {
      padding: 0 var(--space-4);
    }
    
    .legal-section h3 {
      font-size: var(--fs-lg);
    }
  }
</style>